# npm Release & CI/CD

Read `docs/conventions/npm-release.md` before changing publish scripts or release workflows.

## Publish scope

- `NPM_CI_PUBLISH_PACKAGES` must equal `NPM_PUBLISH_ORDER` (all public packages).
- Never shrink the CI publish set without explicit user approval.
- Do not add private-preview shells (`monaco`, `workbench-core`, `shell-react`) to publish order.
- `@workbench-kit/jdw` → directory `packages/json-widget`.

## Two release paths

| Case | Command / trigger |
| --- | --- |
| First release on npm | `publish-packages-local.mjs` (local `npm login`, `--provenance=false`) |
| Version updates | Tag `v*` / `workbench-kit-v*` → `publish.yml` (OIDC only) |

## OIDC — do not regress

- No `NPM_TOKEN` / `NODE_AUTH_TOKEN` in CI publish paths.
- Call `clearNpmRegistryAuth()` before each `npm publish`.
- Unset token env vars in the workflow publish step.
- Do not add `registry-url` to `setup-node` (breaks OIDC).
- Preflight must dry-run all packages on npm, not one probe.

## Versions & dist-tags

- Tag sync sets **all** package versions; skip only when exact `@name@version` already exists on npm.
- Older `@prototype` versions do not block a newer release.
- Default dist-tag is `prototype`, not `latest`. Document `@prototype` for consumers.

## Trusted Publisher

`NewChoBo` / `workbench-kit` / `publish.yml`, Environment blank unless workflow uses a matching GitHub Environment.

## After changes

Run `pnpm format:check` on touched scripts. Prefer CI `workflow_dispatch` dry-run for publish validation.
